cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the application of Super-Resolution (SR) to object detection on satellite data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image processing and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of object detection networks and the YOLOv2 architecture could place the paper under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the application of these techniques to satellite data could also fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
